title: Mountain topography
description: Construct a contour map to display the topography of a mountain region, with 'sandybrown' indicating lower altitudes and 'skyblue' indicating higher altitudes.
solution:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
contour = plt.contourf(x, y, z, cmap='coolwarm')
cbar = plt.colorbar(contour)
cbar.set_label('Altitude (meters)')

plt.contourf(x, y, z, levels=[-1000, -500, 0, 500, 1000], colors=['sandybrown', 'peachpuff', 'lightgreen', 'skyblue'])

plt.title('Topography of a Mountain Region')
plt.xlabel('X Coordinate')
plt.ylabel('Y Coordinate')
plt.show()
